Djibouti Appoints Hadi as Head of Port, Free-Zone Authority

-- B y   M o h a m e d   O s m a n   F a r a h
-- 
2011-07-05T05:20:10Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-05/djibouti-appoints-hadi-as-head-of-port-free-zone-authority.html
Djibouti appointed Aboubaker Omar
Hadi as the head of its  Ports and Free Zones Authority ,
succeeding Aden Ahmed Doualeh.  Hadi previously worked at the Port of Lagos in  Nigeria , the
authority said in a statement yesterday in the capital,
Djibouti.  The port in the Horn of Africa nation is situated on the
Red Sea. The facility provides the only access to the sea for
neighboring Ethiopia, Africaâ€™s second-most populous nation.  To contact the reporter on this story:
